				<h1>Our 33 Most Anticipated Sci-Fi, Fantasy, and Horror Books for the Rest of 2025</h1>
		<h2>In Case You Need More Books to Read...</h2>
    <div class="inner">
		<div class="post_header_wrapper">
    				</div>
				<div class="author_info" itemprop="author" itemscope itemtype="http://schema.org/Person">
			<div class="author_name">By&nbsp;<a href="https://lithub.com/author/drewbroussard/" itemprop="url"><span itemprop="name">Drew&nbsp;Broussard</span></a></div>
			<div class="author_hr"><hr/></div>
			<div class="publish_date">July 8, 2025</div>
		</div>
		<div class="social_links">
						<a href="https://twitter.com/intent/tweet?via=lithub&text=Our+33+Most+Anticipated+Sci-Fi%2C+Fantasy%2C+and+Horror+Books+for+the+Rest+of+2025&url=https%3A%2F%2Flithub.com%2Four-33-most-anticipated-sci-fi-fantasy-and-horror-books-for-the-rest-of-2025%2F"><span class="social_twitter"></span></a>
			<a href="https://www.facebook.com/sharer.php?u=https%3A%2F%2Flithub.com%2Four-33-most-anticipated-sci-fi-fantasy-and-horror-books-for-the-rest-of-2025%2F&t=Our+33+Most+Anticipated+Sci-Fi%2C+Fantasy%2C+and+Horror+Books+for+the+Rest+of+2025"><span class="social_facebook"></span></a>
					</div>
    <div class="inner">
    	<!-- Begin main content -->
    	<div class="inner_wrapper fullwidth">
    			
										<!-- Begin each blog post -->
						<div class="post_wrapper" style="padding-top:0;">
							<div class="post_inner_wrapper">
						    	<div class="post_wrapper_inner">
										<div class="inner_wrapper fullwidth">
								        
										<p>Lit Hub&#8217;s list of the <a href="https://lithub.com/lit-hubs-most-anticipated-books-of-2025-part-two/" target="_blank" rel="noopener">most anticipated books of the second half of the year</a> includes many genre titles, but, one might argue, not enough. What can I say, I&#8217;m an excitable boy, still in love with stories of dragons and spaceships and monsters. And while the darkening world outside can sometimes make it hard to focus on really anything at all, I&#8217;m of the opinion that a bit of true escapism is often what you need to keep the fires burning! Besides, it&#8217;s often genre fiction that holds the truest mirror up to nature, helping us better understand the darkening world and how to fight for light.</p>
<p>So, I present to you here a corollary to the Big List, in the form of a totally idiosyncratic and absolutely non-comprehensive collection of 33 sci-fi, fantasy, and horror books to look forward to in the back half of 2025:</p>
<p style="text-align: center;">*</p>
<p style="text-align: center;"><img fetchpriority="high" decoding="async" data-attachment-id="256659" data-permalink="https://lithub.com/our-33-most-anticipated-sci-fi-fantasy-and-horror-books-for-the-rest-of-2025/attachment/9781960988614/" data-orig-file="https://s26162.pcdn.co/wp-content/uploads/2025/07/9781960988614.avif" data-orig-size="596,921" data-comments-opened="1" data-image-meta="{&quot;aperture&quot;:&quot;0&quot;,&quot;credit&quot;:&quot;&quot;,&quot;camera&quot;:&quot;&quot;,&quot;caption&quot;:&quot;&quot;,&quot;created_timestamp&quot;:&quot;0&quot;,&quot;copyright&quot;:&quot;&quot;,&quot;focal_length&quot;:&quot;0&quot;,&quot;iso&quot;:&quot;0&quot;,&quot;shutter_speed&quot;:&quot;0&quot;,&quot;title&quot;:&quot;&quot;,&quot;orientation&quot;:&quot;0&quot;}" data-image-title="9781960988614" data-image-description="" data-image-caption="" data-medium-file="https://s26162.pcdn.co/wp-content/uploads/2025/07/9781960988614-194x300.jpg" data-large-file="https://s26162.pcdn.co/wp-content/uploads/2025/07/9781960988614.avif" class="aligncenter size-medium wp-image-256659" src="https://s26162.pcdn.co/wp-content/uploads/2025/07/9781960988614-194x300.jpg" alt="" width="194" height="300" srcset="https://s26162.pcdn.co/wp-content/uploads/2025/07/9781960988614-194x300.jpg 194w, https://s26162.pcdn.co/wp-content/uploads/2025/07/9781960988614-39x60.jpg 39w, https://s26162.pcdn.co/wp-content/uploads/2025/07/9781960988614-32x50.jpg 32w, https://s26162.pcdn.co/wp-content/uploads/2025/07/9781960988614.avif 596w" sizes="(max-width: 194px) 100vw, 194px" /></p>
<p style="text-align: center;"><strong>Michael Cisco,Â <em><a href="http://bookshop.org/a/132/9781960988614" class="external" target="_blank">Black Brane</a><br />
</em>CLASH Books, July 22</strong></p>
<p>Michael Cisco is one of those impossible-to-classify writers, whose work is ever-shifting and never even remotely the same. He&#8217;s also probably your favorite weird-fiction writer&#8217;s favorite weird-fiction writer. This new one is a slim shot from CLASH, about a man recovering from a foot injury and remembering his time working for an institute that studied (among other things) black holes. It&#8217;s more or less guaranteed to turn your brain inside out. <em>â€“Drew Broussard, Podcasts Editor and Resident Spooky Wizard</em></p>
<p><img decoding="async" data-attachment-id="256661" data-permalink="https://lithub.com/our-33-most-anticipated-sci-fi-fantasy-and-horror-books-for-the-rest-of-2025/lid_cover_sm-533x800/" data-orig-file="https://s26162.pcdn.co/wp-content/uploads/2025/07/lid_cover_sm-533x800-1.jpg" data-orig-size="533,800" data-comments-opened="1" data-image-meta="{&quot;aperture&quot;:&quot;0&quot;,&quot;credit&quot;:&quot;&quot;,&quot;camera&quot;:&quot;&quot;,&quot;caption&quot;:&quot;&quot;,&quot;created_timestamp&quot;:&quot;0&quot;,&quot;copyright&quot;:&quot;&quot;,&quot;focal_length&quot;:&quot;0&quot;,&quot;iso&quot;:&quot;0&quot;,&quot;shutter_speed&quot;:&quot;0&quot;,&quot;title&quot;:&quot;&quot;,&quot;orientation&quot;:&quot;0&quot;}" data-image-title="lid_cover_sm-533&#215;800" data-image-description="" data-image-caption="" data-medium-file="https://s26162.pcdn.co/wp-content/uploads/2025/07/lid_cover_sm-533x800-1-200x300.jpg" data-large-file="https://s26162.pcdn.co/wp-content/uploads/2025/07/lid_cover_sm-533x800-1.jpg" class="aligncenter size-medium wp-image-256661" src="https://s26162.pcdn.co/wp-content/uploads/2025/07/lid_cover_sm-533x800-1-200x300.jpg" alt="" width="200" height="300" srcset="https://s26162.pcdn.co/wp-content/uploads/2025/07/lid_cover_sm-533x800-1-200x300.jpg 200w, https://s26162.pcdn.co/wp-content/uploads/2025/07/lid_cover_sm-533x800-1-40x60.jpg 40w, https://s26162.pcdn.co/wp-content/uploads/2025/07/lid_cover_sm-533x800-1-33x50.jpg 33w, https://s26162.pcdn.co/wp-content/uploads/2025/07/lid_cover_sm-533x800-1.jpg 533w" sizes="(max-width: 200px) 100vw, 200px" /></p>
<p style="text-align: center;"><strong>John Langan,Â <em><a href="https://wordhorde.com/product/lid-bundle/" class="external" target="_blank">Lost in the Dark and Other Excursions</a><br />
</em>Word Horde, August 5</strong></p>
<p>The bard of Hudson Valley horror returns! Langan continues to rack up an incredible shelf of story collections, each loosely themed to its &#8220;and&#8221;â€”this one promises journeys, quests, Blu-Ray commentary, book endnotes, and more. He is the modern heir to literary horror writers like Washington Irving, Henry James, Nathaniel Hawthorne, and of course Edgar Allan Poeâ€”but honestly he&#8217;s even scarier than any of them. I wait for new Langan books with feverish intensity and will be diving into this as soon as (in)humanly possible. <em>â€“</em><em>DB</em></p>
<h4 style="text-align: left;"><img decoding="async" data-attachment-id="255718" data-permalink="https://lithub.com/lit-hubs-most-anticipated-books-of-2025-part-two/version-1-0-0-48/" data-orig-file="https://s26162.pcdn.co/wp-content/uploads/2025/06/91Yj-6dfaYL.jpg" data-orig-size="1705,2560" data-comments-opened="1" data-image-meta="{&quot;aperture&quot;:&quot;0&quot;,&quot;credit&quot;:&quot;&quot;,&quot;camera&quot;:&quot;&quot;,&quot;caption&quot;:&quot;Version 1.0.0&quot;,&quot;created_timestamp&quot;:&quot;0&quot;,&quot;copyright&quot;:&quot;&quot;,&quot;focal_length&quot;:&quot;0&quot;,&quot;iso&quot;:&quot;0&quot;,&quot;shutter_speed&quot;:&quot;0&quot;,&quot;title&quot;:&quot;Version 1.0.0&quot;,&quot;orientation&quot;:&quot;0&quot;}" data-image-title="Tashan Mehta, Mad Sisters of Esi" data-image-description="" data-image-caption="" data-medium-file="https://s26162.pcdn.co/wp-content/uploads/2025/06/91Yj-6dfaYL-200x300.jpg" data-large-file="https://s26162.pcdn.co/wp-content/uploads/2025/06/91Yj-6dfaYL-682x1024.jpg" class="aligncenter size-medium wp-image-255718" src="https://s26162.pcdn.co/wp-content/uploads/2025/06/91Yj-6dfaYL-200x300.jpg" alt="Tashan Mehta, Mad Sisters of Esi" width="200" height="300" srcset="https://s26162.pcdn.co/wp-content/uploads/2025/06/91Yj-6dfaYL-200x300.jpg 200w, https://s26162.pcdn.co/wp-content/uploads/2025/06/91Yj-6dfaYL-682x1024.jpg 682w, https://s26162.pcdn.co/wp-content/uploads/2025/06/91Yj-6dfaYL-768x1153.jpg 768w, https://s26162.pcdn.co/wp-content/uploads/2025/06/91Yj-6dfaYL-40x60.jpg 40w, https://s26162.pcdn.co/wp-content/uploads/2025/06/91Yj-6dfaYL-1023x1536.jpg 1023w, https://s26162.pcdn.co/wp-content/uploads/2025/06/91Yj-6dfaYL-1364x2048.jpg 1364w, https://s26162.pcdn.co/wp-content/uploads/2025/06/91Yj-6dfaYL-33x50.jpg 33w, https://s26162.pcdn.co/wp-content/uploads/2025/06/91Yj-6dfaYL.jpg 1705w" sizes="(max-width: 200px) 100vw, 200px" /></h4>
<p style="text-align: center;"><strong>Tashan Mehta, <a href="https://bookshop.org/a/132/9780756420062" target="_blank" rel="noopener" class="external"><em>Mad Sisters of Esi</em></a></strong><br />
<strong>DAW, August 5</strong></p>
<p style="text-align: left;">The publicity copy calls <em>Mad Sisters of Esi</em> a cross between <em>Piranesi</em> and Calvino and honestly thatâ€™s enough for me. Add in a dash of multiversal story-centric adventure and really what more do you need? The book has a ton of hype behind it, as it was originally published by HarperCollins India in 2023 and won a handful of awards at the timeâ€”but Iâ€™m avoiding learning anything else about it, because it looks like one of those truly joyful adventures best discovered on the page. <em>â€“</em><em>DB, <a href="https://lithub.com/lit-hubs-most-anticipated-books-of-2025-part-two/">as recommended in our second-half of 2025 list</a></em></p>
<p><img loading="lazy" decoding="async" data-attachment-id="256663" data-permalink="https://lithub.com/our-33-most-anticipated-sci-fi-fantasy-and-horror-books-for-the-rest-of-2025/attachment/9781250357465/" data-orig-file="https://s26162.pcdn.co/wp-content/uploads/2025/07/9781250357465.jpg" data-orig-size="1500,2400" data-comments-opened="1" data-image-meta="{&quot;aperture&quot;:&quot;0&quot;,&quot;credit&quot;:&quot;&quot;,&quot;camera&quot;:&quot;&quot;,&quot;caption&quot;:&quot;&quot;,&quot;created_timestamp&quot;:&quot;0&quot;,&quot;copyright&quot;:&quot;&quot;,&quot;focal_length&quot;:&quot;0&quot;,&quot;iso&quot;:&quot;0&quot;,&quot;shutter_speed&quot;:&quot;0&quot;,&quot;title&quot;:&quot;&quot;,&quot;orientation&quot;:&quot;0&quot;}" data-image-title="9781250357465" data-image-description="" data-image-caption="" data-medium-file="https://s26162.pcdn.co/wp-content/uploads/2025/07/9781250357465-188x300.jpg" data-large-file="https://s26162.pcdn.co/wp-content/uploads/2025/07/9781250357465-640x1024.jpg" class="aligncenter size-medium wp-image-256663" src="https://s26162.pcdn.co/wp-content/uploads/2025/07/9781250357465-188x300.jpg" alt="" width="188" height="300" srcset="https://s26162.pcdn.co/wp-content/uploads/2025/07/9781250357465-188x300.jpg 188w, https://s26162.pcdn.co/wp-content/uploads/2025/07/9781250357465-640x1024.jpg 640w, https://s26162.pcdn.co/wp-content/uploads/2025/07/9781250357465-768x1229.jpg 768w, https://s26162.pcdn.co/wp-content/uploads/2025/07/9781250357465-38x60.jpg 38w, https://s26162.pcdn.co/wp-content/uploads/2025/07/9781250357465-960x1536.jpg 960w, https://s26162.pcdn.co/wp-content/uploads/2025/07/9781250357465-1280x2048.jpg 1280w, https://s26162.pcdn.co/wp-content/uploads/2025/07/9781250357465-31x50.jpg 31w, https://s26162.pcdn.co/wp-content/uploads/2025/07/9781250357465.jpg 1500w" sizes="auto, (max-width: 188px) 100vw, 188px" /></p>
<p style="text-align: center;"><strong>Annalee Newitz,Â <em><a href="http://bookshop.org/a/132/9781250357465" class="external" target="_blank">Automatic Noodle</a><br />
</em>Tordotcom, August 5</strong></p>
<p>&#8220;Cozy&#8221; is a divisive word in some parts of the genre community these days, but Newitz delivers a delightful read that manages to deliver feel-good vibes (robots start their own noodle shop! And triumph over bigotry!) while not condescending to its readership by pretending that the world outside doesn&#8217;t exist. Somehow it packs in an honest and compelling interrogation of: sentience/robot intelligence, the ethics of capitalist ownership, the joys of cooking, the pleasure of doing something for someone else, and more. Also, <a href="https://www.automaticnoodle.website/" class="external" target="_blank">I want a t-shirt</a>! Good swag! <em>â€“</em><em>DB</em></p>
<p style="text-align: left;"><img loading="lazy" decoding="async" data-attachment-id="256618" data-permalink="https://lithub.com/our-33-most-anticipated-sci-fi-fantasy-and-horror-books-for-the-rest-of-2025/a-game-in-yellow-199x300/" data-orig-file="https://s26162.pcdn.co/wp-content/uploads/2025/07/A-Game-in-Yellow-199x300-1.jpg" data-orig-size="199,300" data-comments-opened="1" data-image-meta="{&quot;aperture&quot;:&quot;0&quot;,&quot;credit&quot;:&quot;&quot;,&quot;camera&quot;:&quot;&quot;,&quot;caption&quot;:&quot;&quot;,&quot;created_timestamp&quot;:&quot;0&quot;,&quot;copyright&quot;:&quot;&quot;,&quot;focal_length&quot;:&quot;0&quot;,&quot;iso&quot;:&quot;0&quot;,&quot;shutter_speed&quot;:&quot;0&quot;,&quot;title&quot;:&quot;&quot;,&quot;orientation&quot;:&quot;0&quot;}" data-image-title="A-Game-in-Yellow-199&#215;300" data-image-description="&lt;p&gt;A Game in Yellow by Hailey Piper&lt;/p&gt;
" data-image-caption="" data-medium-file="https://s26162.pcdn.co/wp-content/uploads/2025/07/A-Game-in-Yellow-199x300-1.jpg" data-large-file="https://s26162.pcdn.co/wp-content/uploads/2025/07/A-Game-in-Yellow-199x300-1.jpg" class="aligncenter size-full wp-image-256618" src="https://s26162.pcdn.co/wp-content/uploads/2025/07/A-Game-in-Yellow-199x300-1.jpg" alt="" width="199" height="300" srcset="https://s26162.pcdn.co/wp-content/uploads/2025/07/A-Game-in-Yellow-199x300-1.jpg 199w, https://s26162.pcdn.co/wp-content/uploads/2025/07/A-Game-in-Yellow-199x300-1-40x60.jpg 40w, https://s26162.pcdn.co/wp-content/uploads/2025/07/A-Game-in-Yellow-199x300-1-33x50.jpg 33w" sizes="auto, (max-width: 199px) 100vw, 199px" /></p>
<p style="text-align: center;"><strong>Hailey Piper,Â <em><a class="external" href="https://bookshop.org/a/238/9781668077092" target="_blank" rel="noopener">A Game in Yellow</a></em></strong><br />
<strong>S&amp;S/Saga Press, August 12</strong></p>
<p style="text-align: left;"><em>The King In Yellow</em> is the seed of inspiration for Hailey Piperâ€™s batshit erotic horror thriller, in which a lesbian couple looking to spice things up goes down a hellish rabbit-hole when they discover a disturbing masterpiece that gives dark pleasures in small doses, and delivers death to those who ask for a bigger slice. <em>â€“</em><em>Molly Odintz, CrimeReads Managing Editor, <a href="https://crimereads.com/25-new-and-upcoming-horror-novels-to-look-out-for-this-summer-and-beyond/">as recommended at CrimeReads</a></em></p>
<p><img loading="lazy" decoding="async" data-attachment-id="256666" data-permalink="https://lithub.com/our-33-most-anticipated-sci-fi-fantasy-and-horror-books-for-the-rest-of-2025/attachment/9781668057551/" data-orig-file="https://s26162.pcdn.co/wp-content/uploads/2025/07/9781668057551.jpg" data-orig-size="663,1000" data-comments-opened="1" data-image-meta="{&quot;aperture&quot;:&quot;0&quot;,&quot;credit&quot;:&quot;&quot;,&quot;camera&quot;:&quot;&quot;,&quot;caption&quot;:&quot;&quot;,&quot;created_timestamp&quot;:&quot;0&quot;,&quot;copyright&quot;:&quot;&quot;,&quot;focal_length&quot;:&quot;0&quot;,&quot;iso&quot;:&quot;0&quot;,&quot;shutter_speed&quot;:&quot;0&quot;,&quot;title&quot;:&quot;&quot;,&quot;orientation&quot;:&quot;0&quot;}" data-image-title="9781668057551" data-image-description="" data-image-caption="" data-medium-file="https://s26162.pcdn.co/wp-content/uploads/2025/07/9781668057551-199x300.jpg" data-large-file="https://s26162.pcdn.co/wp-content/uploads/2025/07/9781668057551.jpg" class="aligncenter size-medium wp-image-256666" src="https://s26162.pcdn.co/wp-content/uploads/2025/07/9781668057551-199x300.jpg" alt="" width="199" height="300" srcset="https://s26162.pcdn.co/wp-content/uploads/2025/07/9781668057551-199x300.jpg 199w, https://s26162.pcdn.co/wp-content/uploads/2025/07/9781668057551-40x60.jpg 40w, https://s26162.pcdn.co/wp-content/uploads/2025/07/9781668057551-33x50.jpg 33w, https://s26162.pcdn.co/wp-content/uploads/2025/07/9781668057551.jpg 663w" sizes="auto, (max-width: 199px) 100vw, 199px" /></p>
