<p style="text-align: center;"><strong>Hiron Ennes,Â <a href="http://bookshop.org/a/132/9781250811219" class="external" target="_blank"><em>The Works of Vermin</em></a><br />
Tor Books, October 14</strong></p>
<p>I loved Ennes&#8217;s <em>Leech</em> but was surprised by just howÂ <em>desperately</em> I loved thisâ€”I started reading it on a Sunday and finished it feverishly the next night. For any reader who longs to visit Ambergris, New Crobuzon, Luriat, Hav, Ravicka&#8230; pack your bags for Tiliard. Ennes&#8217;s new novel is an epic fantasy set in a rotting city infested with bugs where opera soloists fight duels to the death onstage and perfumers craft scents to warp reality. Truly on par with Vandermeer and MiÃ©ville, an absolute thrill to read. <em>â€“</em><em>DB</em></p>
