</em>S&amp;S / Saga Press, October 21</strong></p>
<p>I&#8217;m loving Saga&#8217;s decision to revive the old Ace Doubles format this year (following, it should be noted, in the footsteps of the fabulous Tenebrous Press Split Scream seriesâ€”and, I suppose, Catherine Lacey&#8217;s <a href="https://bookshop.org/a/132/9780374615406" target="_blank" rel="noopener" class="external"><em>The MÃ¶bius Book</em></a>, although that&#8217;s kinda different)â€”the first was a Stephen Graham Jones double-header, then a Day/Night-themed Ellen Datlow-edited story collection, but this is where the rubber should meet the road for the format: two brand new novellas from absolute SF stars. I can&#8217;t wait to read them both, and to flip the book in-between! <em>â€“</em><em>DB</em></p>
<p><img loading="lazy" decoding="async" data-attachment-id="255973" data-permalink="https://lithub.com/lit-hubs-most-anticipated-books-of-2025-part-two/the-everlasting-4/" data-orig-file="https://s26162.pcdn.co/wp-content/uploads/2025/06/the-everlasting-4.jpg" data-orig-size="1200,1812" data-comments-opened="1" data-image-meta="{&quot;aperture&quot;:&quot;0&quot;,&quot;credit&quot;:&quot;&quot;,&quot;camera&quot;:&quot;&quot;,&quot;caption&quot;:&quot;&quot;,&quot;created_timestamp&quot;:&quot;0&quot;,&quot;copyright&quot;:&quot;&quot;,&quot;focal_length&quot;:&quot;0&quot;,&quot;iso&quot;:&quot;0&quot;,&quot;shutter_speed&quot;:&quot;0&quot;,&quot;title&quot;:&quot;&quot;,&quot;orientation&quot;:&quot;0&quot;}" data-image-title="Alix E. Harrow, The Everlasting" data-image-description="" data-image-caption="" data-medium-file="https://s26162.pcdn.co/wp-content/uploads/2025/06/the-everlasting-4-199x300.jpg" data-large-file="https://s26162.pcdn.co/wp-content/uploads/2025/06/the-everlasting-4-678x1024.jpg" class="aligncenter size-medium wp-image-255973" src="https://s26162.pcdn.co/wp-content/uploads/2025/06/the-everlasting-4-199x300.jpg" alt="Alix E. Harrow, The Everlasting" width="199" height="300" srcset="https://s26162.pcdn.co/wp-content/uploads/2025/06/the-everlasting-4-199x300.jpg 199w, https://s26162.pcdn.co/wp-content/uploads/2025/06/the-everlasting-4-678x1024.jpg 678w, https://s26162.pcdn.co/wp-content/uploads/2025/06/the-everlasting-4-768x1160.jpg 768w, https://s26162.pcdn.co/wp-content/uploads/2025/06/the-everlasting-4-40x60.jpg 40w, https://s26162.pcdn.co/wp-content/uploads/2025/06/the-everlasting-4-1017x1536.jpg 1017w, https://s26162.pcdn.co/wp-content/uploads/2025/06/the-everlasting-4-33x50.jpg 33w, https://s26162.pcdn.co/wp-content/uploads/2025/06/the-everlasting-4.jpg 1200w" sizes="auto, (max-width: 199px) 100vw, 199px" /></p>
<p style="text-align: center;"><strong>Alix E. Harrow, <a href="https://bookshop.org/a/132/9781250799081" target="_blank" rel="noopener" class="external"><em>The Everlasting</em> </a></strong><br />
<strong>Tor, October 28</strong></p>
<p>Harrow-heads already know that sheâ€™s one of the best fantasy writers workingâ€”but this new book is a time-twisting Courtly Romance (an academic is thrown back in time to accompany his countryâ€™s most famous knight on her final crusade) with sneaky-deep reflections on storytelling, truth, power, and love that promises to be her best yet. Iâ€™ll follow Alix Harrow wherever she goes.Â <em>â€“DB, <a href="https://lithub.com/lit-hubs-most-anticipated-books-of-2025-part-two/">as recommended in our second-half of 2025 list</a></em></p>
<p><img loading="lazy" decoding="async" data-attachment-id="256684" data-permalink="https://lithub.com/our-33-most-anticipated-sci-fi-fantasy-and-horror-books-for-the-rest-of-2025/cover-to-be-revealed-template/" data-orig-file="https://s26162.pcdn.co/wp-content/uploads/2025/07/Long-Low-Whistle-Laurel-Hightower.jpg" data-orig-size="1707,2560" data-comments-opened="1" data-image-meta="{&quot;aperture&quot;:&quot;0&quot;,&quot;credit&quot;:&quot;&quot;,&quot;camera&quot;:&quot;&quot;,&quot;caption&quot;:&quot;&quot;,&quot;created_timestamp&quot;:&quot;1741108726&quot;,&quot;copyright&quot;:&quot;&quot;,&quot;focal_length&quot;:&quot;0&quot;,&quot;iso&quot;:&quot;0&quot;,&quot;shutter_speed&quot;:&quot;0&quot;,&quot;title&quot;:&quot;Cover To Be Revealed TEMPLATE&quot;,&quot;orientation&quot;:&quot;0&quot;}" data-image-title="Cover To Be Revealed TEMPLATE" data-image-description="" data-image-caption="" data-medium-file="https://s26162.pcdn.co/wp-content/uploads/2025/07/Long-Low-Whistle-Laurel-Hightower-200x300.jpg" data-large-file="https://s26162.pcdn.co/wp-content/uploads/2025/07/Long-Low-Whistle-Laurel-Hightower-683x1024.jpg" class="aligncenter size-medium wp-image-256684" src="https://s26162.pcdn.co/wp-content/uploads/2025/07/Long-Low-Whistle-Laurel-Hightower-200x300.jpg" alt="" width="200" height="300" srcset="https://s26162.pcdn.co/wp-content/uploads/2025/07/Long-Low-Whistle-Laurel-Hightower-200x300.jpg 200w, https://s26162.pcdn.co/wp-content/uploads/2025/07/Long-Low-Whistle-Laurel-Hightower-683x1024.jpg 683w, https://s26162.pcdn.co/wp-content/uploads/2025/07/Long-Low-Whistle-Laurel-Hightower-768x1152.jpg 768w, https://s26162.pcdn.co/wp-content/uploads/2025/07/Long-Low-Whistle-Laurel-Hightower-40x60.jpg 40w, https://s26162.pcdn.co/wp-content/uploads/2025/07/Long-Low-Whistle-Laurel-Hightower-1024x1536.jpg 1024w, https://s26162.pcdn.co/wp-content/uploads/2025/07/Long-Low-Whistle-Laurel-Hightower-1366x2048.jpg 1366w, https://s26162.pcdn.co/wp-content/uploads/2025/07/Long-Low-Whistle-Laurel-Hightower-33x50.jpg 33w, https://s26162.pcdn.co/wp-content/uploads/2025/07/Long-Low-Whistle-Laurel-Hightower.jpg 1707w" sizes="auto, (max-width: 200px) 100vw, 200px" /></p>
<p style="text-align: center;"><strong>Laurel Hightower,Â <em><a href="https://shortwavepublishing.com/catalog/the-long-low-whistle-killer-vhs-7-by-laurel-hightower/" class="external" target="_blank">The Long Low Whistle</a><br />
</em>Shortwave Publishing, November 4</strong></p>
<p>Some of the coolest stuff happening in genre publishing is coming out of little presses doing neat projectsâ€”and Shortwave&#8217;sÂ <em>Killer VHS Series</em> is one of the gold standards. Each book is meant to evoke video-store weird B-movie energy and from holiday slashers to creature-features, they&#8217;ve knocked it out of the park so far. The newest promises cryptid hunters and spooky mines and I&#8217;ll read it like I would&#8217;ve watched it: late at night, half-scared and half-delighted. <em>â€“</em><em>DB</em></p>
<p><img loading="lazy" decoding="async" data-attachment-id="256686" data-permalink="https://lithub.com/our-33-most-anticipated-sci-fi-fantasy-and-horror-books-for-the-rest-of-2025/9780593983751-2/" data-orig-file="https://s26162.pcdn.co/wp-content/uploads/2025/07/9780593983751.jpg" data-orig-size="300,450" data-comments-opened="1" data-image-meta="{&quot;aperture&quot;:&quot;0&quot;,&quot;credit&quot;:&quot;&quot;,&quot;camera&quot;:&quot;&quot;,&quot;caption&quot;:&quot;&quot;,&quot;created_timestamp&quot;:&quot;0&quot;,&quot;copyright&quot;:&quot;&quot;,&quot;focal_length&quot;:&quot;0&quot;,&quot;iso&quot;:&quot;0&quot;,&quot;shutter_speed&quot;:&quot;0&quot;,&quot;title&quot;:&quot;&quot;,&quot;orientation&quot;:&quot;0&quot;}" data-image-title="9780593983751" data-image-description="" data-image-caption="" data-medium-file="https://s26162.pcdn.co/wp-content/uploads/2025/07/9780593983751-200x300.jpg" data-large-file="https://s26162.pcdn.co/wp-content/uploads/2025/07/9780593983751.jpg" class="aligncenter size-medium wp-image-256686" src="https://s26162.pcdn.co/wp-content/uploads/2025/07/9780593983751-200x300.jpg" alt="" width="200" height="300" srcset="https://s26162.pcdn.co/wp-content/uploads/2025/07/9780593983751-200x300.jpg 200w, https://s26162.pcdn.co/wp-content/uploads/2025/07/9780593983751-40x60.jpg 40w, https://s26162.pcdn.co/wp-content/uploads/2025/07/9780593983751-33x50.jpg 33w, https://s26162.pcdn.co/wp-content/uploads/2025/07/9780593983751.jpg 300w" sizes="auto, (max-width: 200px) 100vw, 200px" /></p>
<p style="text-align: center;"><strong>QNTM, <em><a href="http://bookshop.org/a/132/9780593983751" class="external" target="_blank">There is No Antimemetics Division</a><br />
</em>Ballantine, November 11</strong></p>
<p>I&#8217;m <a href="https://lithub.com/the-38-best-books-we-read-in-2023/">on record in these pages</a> as being an enormous fan of QNTM&#8217;s <em>There is No Antimemetics Division</em>â€”and I&#8217;m so excited that it&#8217;s getting a major-pub re-release, and even more excited that QNTM has extensively revised and deepened this strange novel. As I said in 2023: Imagine, if you can, an entity that it can immediately erase any knowledge of its existence from the minds of anyone who encounters it. Now try to imagine that youâ€™re one of the few people working for an organization trying to defend humanity from such an entityâ€”but you can barely remember the gig, because of the aforementioned memory erasure. Welcome to the antimemetics division; no, this is not your first day. <em>â€“</em><em>DB</em></p>
<p><img loading="lazy" decoding="async" data-attachment-id="256687" data-permalink="https://lithub.com/our-33-most-anticipated-sci-fi-fantasy-and-horror-books-for-the-rest-of-2025/untitled-2-5/" data-orig-file="https://s26162.pcdn.co/wp-content/uploads/2025/07/Untitled-2.png" data-orig-size="421,578" data-comments-opened="1" data-image-meta="{&quot;aperture&quot;:&quot;0&quot;,&quot;credit&quot;:&quot;&quot;,&quot;camera&quot;:&quot;&quot;,&quot;caption&quot;:&quot;&quot;,&quot;created_timestamp&quot;:&quot;0&quot;,&quot;copyright&quot;:&quot;&quot;,&quot;focal_length&quot;:&quot;0&quot;,&quot;iso&quot;:&quot;0&quot;,&quot;shutter_speed&quot;:&quot;0&quot;,&quot;title&quot;:&quot;&quot;,&quot;orientation&quot;:&quot;0&quot;}" data-image-title="Untitled 2" data-image-description="" data-image-caption="" data-medium-file="https://s26162.pcdn.co/wp-content/uploads/2025/07/Untitled-2-219x300.png" data-large-file="https://s26162.pcdn.co/wp-content/uploads/2025/07/Untitled-2.png" class="aligncenter size-medium wp-image-256687" src="https://s26162.pcdn.co/wp-content/uploads/2025/07/Untitled-2-219x300.png" alt="" width="219" height="300" srcset="https://s26162.pcdn.co/wp-content/uploads/2025/07/Untitled-2-219x300.png 219w, https://s26162.pcdn.co/wp-content/uploads/2025/07/Untitled-2-44x60.png 44w, https://s26162.pcdn.co/wp-content/uploads/2025/07/Untitled-2-36x50.png 36w, https://s26162.pcdn.co/wp-content/uploads/2025/07/Untitled-2.png 421w" sizes="auto, (max-width: 219px) 100vw, 219px" /></p>
<p style="text-align: center;"><strong>Sam Munson,Â <em><a href="http://bookshop.org/a/132/9781953387974" class="external" target="_blank">The Sofa</a><br />
</em>Two Dollar Radio, November 11</strong></p>
<p>A family comes back from vacation to find that their sofa is&#8230;. different. Things will almost certainly get weirder from there, because it&#8217;s a Two Dollar Radio book and it&#8217;s a Sam Munson book. I can&#8217;t wait. <em>â€“</em><em>DB</em></p>
<p><img loading="lazy" decoding="async" data-attachment-id="256690" data-permalink="https://lithub.com/our-33-most-anticipated-sci-fi-fantasy-and-horror-books-for-the-rest-of-2025/image-200x300/" data-orig-file="https://s26162.pcdn.co/wp-content/uploads/2025/07/image-200x300-1.png" data-orig-size="200,300" data-comments-opened="1" data-image-meta="{&quot;aperture&quot;:&quot;0&quot;,&quot;credit&quot;:&quot;&quot;,&quot;camera&quot;:&quot;&quot;,&quot;caption&quot;:&quot;&quot;,&quot;created_timestamp&quot;:&quot;0&quot;,&quot;copyright&quot;:&quot;&quot;,&quot;focal_length&quot;:&quot;0&quot;,&quot;iso&quot;:&quot;0&quot;,&quot;shutter_speed&quot;:&quot;0&quot;,&quot;title&quot;:&quot;&quot;,&quot;orientation&quot;:&quot;0&quot;}" data-image-title="image-200&#215;300" data-image-description="" data-image-caption="" data-medium-file="https://s26162.pcdn.co/wp-content/uploads/2025/07/image-200x300-1.png" data-large-file="https://s26162.pcdn.co/wp-content/uploads/2025/07/image-200x300-1.png" class="aligncenter size-full wp-image-256690" src="https://s26162.pcdn.co/wp-content/uploads/2025/07/image-200x300-1.png" alt="" width="200" height="300" srcset="https://s26162.pcdn.co/wp-content/uploads/2025/07/image-200x300-1.png 200w, https://s26162.pcdn.co/wp-content/uploads/2025/07/image-200x300-1-40x60.png 40w, https://s26162.pcdn.co/wp-content/uploads/2025/07/image-200x300-1-33x50.png 33w" sizes="auto, (max-width: 200px) 100vw, 200px" /></p>
<p style="text-align: center;"><strong>Rascal Hartley, <em>Dear Stupid Penpal<br />
</em>Tenebrous Press, November 12</strong></p>
<p>An angry astronaut discovers that, as time dilates on his trip and those he and his crew left behind have all died, his penpal back home inexplicably survives. Tenebrous continues to acquire strange and genre-wobbling books, and this one should bring horror and pathos and old-school space-faring SF in equal measure. <em>â€“</em><em>DB</em></p>
<p><img loading="lazy" decoding="async" data-attachment-id="256688" data-permalink="https://lithub.com/our-33-most-anticipated-sci-fi-fantasy-and-horror-books-for-the-rest-of-2025/attachment/207704242/" data-orig-file="https://s26162.pcdn.co/wp-content/uploads/2025/07/207704242.jpg" data-orig-size="1002,1500" data-comments-opened="1" data-image-meta="{&quot;aperture&quot;:&quot;0&quot;,&quot;credit&quot;:&quot;&quot;,&quot;camera&quot;:&quot;&quot;,&quot;caption&quot;:&quot;&quot;,&quot;created_timestamp&quot;:&quot;0&quot;,&quot;copyright&quot;:&quot;&quot;,&quot;focal_length&quot;:&quot;0&quot;,&quot;iso&quot;:&quot;0&quot;,&quot;shutter_speed&quot;:&quot;0&quot;,&quot;title&quot;:&quot;&quot;,&quot;orientation&quot;:&quot;0&quot;}" data-image-title="207704242" data-image-description="" data-image-caption="" data-medium-file="https://s26162.pcdn.co/wp-content/uploads/2025/07/207704242-200x300.jpg" data-large-file="https://s26162.pcdn.co/wp-content/uploads/2025/07/207704242-684x1024.jpg" class="aligncenter size-medium wp-image-256688" src="https://s26162.pcdn.co/wp-content/uploads/2025/07/207704242-200x300.jpg" alt="" width="200" height="300" srcset="https://s26162.pcdn.co/wp-content/uploads/2025/07/207704242-200x300.jpg 200w, https://s26162.pcdn.co/wp-content/uploads/2025/07/207704242-684x1024.jpg 684w, https://s26162.pcdn.co/wp-content/uploads/2025/07/207704242-768x1150.jpg 768w, https://s26162.pcdn.co/wp-content/uploads/2025/07/207704242-40x60.jpg 40w, https://s26162.pcdn.co/wp-content/uploads/2025/07/207704242-33x50.jpg 33w, https://s26162.pcdn.co/wp-content/uploads/2025/07/207704242.jpg 1002w" sizes="auto, (max-width: 200px) 100vw, 200px" /></p>
<p style="text-align: center;"><strong>Georgia Summers,Â <em><a href="http://bookshop.org/a/132/9780316561839" class="external" target="_blank">The Bookshop Below</a><br />
</em>Orbit, November 18</strong></p>
<p>For all the book-lovers out there, all the dreamers who wish for their own bookstore, who feel that there&#8217;s a magical connection to books themselves&#8230; getÂ <em>The Bookshop Below</em> onto your stack ASAP. A classic adventure story with mysterious shady organizations and magical books &amp; bookstores and slow-burning romance. Between this and <em>The City of Stardust</em>, Summers is staking her claim as one of the great joyful-fantasy novelists. It&#8217;ll make you happy. <em>â€“</em><em>DB</em></p>
										
																				
																		
